boundary dog
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a dog housed near a boundary prior to fencing, or chained to a gateway in a boundary fence to prevent stock wandering, prior to roads being fenced.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: dog shepherd; fence dog
